      <hedline>
        <hl1>Soprano's Piano</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Voytek Matushevski letter takes issue with assertion in August 20 travel article that opera singer Marcella Sembrich is virtually forgotten today (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I would take issue with the assertion in the article that Marcella Sembrich is ''virtually forgotten'' today. Her career at the Metropolitan Opera (1883-1909) was one of the longest. Also, after her retirement from the opera, Marcella Sembrich was a central figure (together with Paderewski) in re-establishing the independence of Poland.</p>
        <p>VOYTEK MATUSHEVSKI  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
